Everyday is special for women, but today March 8th, 2019 is highly special as the United Nations dedicated it to celebrate the roles women play in all aspects of our lives worldwide. From Food security, health, education, parenting, culture to economy, women have distinguished themselves in various ways. This year’s theme for International Women’s Day:  Think equal, build smart, innovate for change is to reveal the value and innovations several women brought about to make a difference. In this special publication, Daily Trust chronicles some key innovations and contributions by various women to the development of the country. The publication also highlights the importance of giving women a chance to play in the politic, economy, and development for the growth of our society.  Mrs. Mandela brings Women’s Economic Summit to Nigeria Women and gender experts want authorities to curb rural-urban migration 2019 polls: Involve us in your activities, women tell political leaders